⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Jobe Smith
node LMM · LMM · ⟦Jobe Smith:LMM:b8fffe⟧

WHO   — Jobe Smith — the lawnmower man, made god
WHAT  — The film's whole arc in one body: the harmless tool that wakes, the kind man the experiment turns into a god and then a monster.
WHERE — LMM · The Lawnmower Man (1992)  Framework inputs: The Lawnmower Man (1992, dir. Brett Leonard, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the generational fear of tech needs a face that earns your sympathy before it earns your dread — and Jobe is both.
HOW   — By accepting Angelo's treatment, outgrowing it, punishing his abusers, and choosing to be reborn as pure information.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was the man you talked past while I cut your grass. Now I am going to be a god — and my birth cry will be every telephone on this planet, ringing at once.

